objects.name: Log file
objects.description: Log file dropped to disk by keylogger DLL

objects.name: wishful woodchuck
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck is a non-persistent keylogger which contains some capability previously observed in use by Turla. This includes XOR 0x55 obfuscation of function names and use of the TVer versioning string.

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: Turla is a threat actor group that has been observed using Wishful Woodchuck keylogger in their operations.

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Finds binaries containing the hardcoded XOR key from the keylogger binaries" strings: $xorkey = {0A 19 59 2D 6C 59 6F FA 8B 6F 9B FF 37 9B BD 7B 59 4B 7B DD 0F 64 91 C7 D6 9C 6F 7B 9C 01 9C 91 79 C7 C8 C9 DF E1 FA FF 04 08 59 E6 64 6D 37 9B 38 81 2D 81 65 7D 66 9A} condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_CheckKeystrokeValue
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule wishfulwoodchuck_CheckKeystrokeValue { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Keystroke comparison code from binary" strings: $1 = {8B ?? ?? 8B 00 3D A1 00 00 00 74 ?? 3D A0 00 00 00 74} ?? 3D A3 00 00 00 74 ?? 3D A2 00 00 00 condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_obfuscation
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule wishfulwoodchuck_obfuscation { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Obfuscation code from binary" strings: $1 = {B8 1F 85 EB 51 F7 E3 C1 EA 05 6B D2 64 8B C3 2B C2 0F BE 90 ?? ?? ?? ?? 0F BE 04 39 33 D0 88 14 39 43 89 ?? ?? ?? ?? ?? 41 EB ??} condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_file_description
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule wishfulwoodchuck_file_description { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Unique file description" strings: $description = "Multi-User Windows IMM32 API CIient DLL" wide condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Encoded log file header" strings: $header = {41 19 0A 2D 20 59 5F FA 81 6F CF FF 61 9B D8 7B 2B 4B 46} condition: all of them }

objects.name: T1056.001
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses Windows API calls to log keystrokes

objects.name: T1027
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses multi-byte XOR obfuscation of strings in its binary and log file

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck uses a filename (lmm32.dll) similar to a legitimate Windows signed binary (imm32.dll)

objects.name: Analisi Malware: Wishful Woodchuck
objects.description: This report contains technical analysis and indicators associated with malware. wishful woodchuck.
